Change to coldboot, to clear up to 4MB in STPAD.
----------------------------
revision 2.43
date: 1992/02/12 01:32:40;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +27 -5
Fixed an RTS/CTS bug in SCC code. See scc_sender.
----------------------------
revision 2.42
date: 1991/11/14 23:51:46;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +16 -3
Added a comment about hidden interaction between ikbdws and ikbdput.
----------------------------
revision 2.41
date: 1991/11/14 23:42:20;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +33 -17
Fixed two bugs reported from Germany.  First, the wrong argument was
pulled off the stack in the SCC Rsconf code, so you couldn't cause a
break as documented.  Second, the "wait 5ms using a trick" code in
ikbdwc had two problems, one of logic and one of implementation.
Now both work.
----------------------------
revision 2.40
date: 1991/10/22 19:25:30;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +11 -2
Added a moveq to pre-clear d0 in the Midi Bconin code.  Until now,
Bconin on MIDI always returned $FFFFFFxx.  Sadly this didn't make it
into 3.06 or 2.06.  Sigh.
----------------------------
revision 2.39
date: 1991/10/15 14:08:24;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +9 -2
Changed Bioskeys so it does something else, too: it nukes
key repeat.  In the first place, there was no way to do this
(and it's necessary for STBOOK), and in the second place, this
is not an unreasonable place to do it, since key repeat is based
on scan code and you're ostensibly changing the tables with this
call.
----------------------------
revision 2.38
date: 1991/09/16 23:44:52;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +10 -7
Fixed jdisabint twice: first, you can't clear ipra using bclr: it's an
asynchronous register.  Second, my "fix" back in 89 for clearing isr was
wrong -- I used asl, not rol, so we were clearing the isr for the interrupt
in question and all the lower bits in the same isr.  Sigh.
----------------------------
revision 2.37
date: 1991/09/12 19:41:34;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +25 -34
Changed conditionals: ! is bitwise in MAS, so !TT is $FFFFFFFE when TT is 1.
So we use (TT == 0) instead.  Sigh.
----------------------------
revision 2.36
date: 1991/09/06 14:50:56;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +118 -116
Changed all "ifne" to "if" and "ifeq" to "if !" and "endc" to "endif."
----------------------------
revision 2.35
date: 1991/08/05 15:26:53;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +20 -2
Modified coldboot code for STPAD
----------------------------
revision 2.34
date: 1991/06/20 14:06:47;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +8 -48
Removed new keyboard code (was conditional on OLDIKBD)
because I found a way to hook in a TSR to fix overrun without
changing the keyboard code.
----------------------------
revision 2.33
date: 1991/06/13 16:29:56;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +59 -8
Added alt-keypad functionality: hold down ALT, type a decimal number on the
keypad, and let go of alt to get that ASCII code into the keyboard buffer. 
The result has zero as the scan code and the kbshift value at the moment
you let go of ALT (so you can't get ALT itself in there).
----------------------------
revision 2.32
date: 1991/05/21 16:54:10;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +61 -9
Changed error handling in midi/ikbd so I could hook in a TSR to fix the
overrun problems.  The overrun fixing might one day be part of the OS.  The
change is that the error handler in ikbdvecs gets control BEFORE the byte
has been read from the chip, so it must read the data to clear the error. 
Also, if there is an error, the data byte is not presumed valid and is not
used.  Set OLDIKBD to 1 to get the old behavior back.

----------------------------
revision 2.31
date: 1991/04/26 17:44:39;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +5 -6
Removed the STPAD conditional around MIDI code.  Bconmap probably isn't as
unconditional as it's cracked up to be: it's not been tested when neither
STPLUS nor TT is true.

----------------------------
revision 2.30
date: 1991/04/11 12:13:54;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +6 -3
Removed PAL condition from spain -- now it's always PAL.
----------------------------
revision 2.29
date: 1991/04/02 12:34:47;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +22 -12
Folded in some more things from SERPTCH. This is the version for 3.06.
----------------------------
revision 2.28
date: 1991/03/27 12:33:58;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +14 -6
Turned on Bconmap for TT+STPLUS rather than just TT. It should really be on
for ANYTHING.  Also, a bug fix in RSCONF for MFP's: was writing rsmode in
iorec as word, not byte.  Could be other problems which I haven't handled
yet, but which are fixed by SERPTCH.

Took out midi part of ikbd/midi interrupt if STPAD, since pad has no MIDI.
----------------------------
revision 2.27
date: 1991/01/31 13:50:17;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +67 -14
Fixed some bugs in serial port handling for SCC.
----------------------------
revision 2.26
date: 1990/10/15 12:08:02;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +26 -18
Fixed keyboard tables so they're right: the arrow keys for some countries
did NOT give ASCII codes of digits when shifted, as the VDI spec says
they should.  Also, shifted numeric keypad keys gave punctuation
in some countries, which was wrong.

Also removed PC-relative addressing because MAS has a bug: PC-relative
addressing to a label that's BEFORE the PC, with arithmetic, generates
incorrect code.  Example: "move.b label+1(PC),d0" when 'label' is before
the current PC generates "move.b label+3(PC),d0"
----------------------------
revision 2.25
date: 1990/08/21 17:18:59;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +136 -278
Mega STe support added.

Bconmap is no longer conditional.

Osconf is now an EQU exported from here to startup.s, so that file
isn't country-dependent any more.
----------------------------
revision 2.24
date: 1990/08/03 15:18:09;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +6 -3
Fixed an oops in Norway's keyboard table: REAL TTOS FINAL RELEASE!
----------------------------
revision 2.23
date: 1990/08/03 13:21:50;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +14 -2
TTOS FINAL RELEASE
----------------------------
revision 2.22
date: 1990/07/19 14:46:56;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +33 -4
Fixed a bug in rsconf: -2 for TT MFP's port always returned rate
for ST MFP.  Now it is right.  Also sped up memory clearing in
coldboot.

Added a thing that Insignia needs for their SoftPC product: a vector
BEFORE Kbdvbase() which is jmp'ed through when the BIOS has established
that a scan code from the keyboard is a make or break code from a key,
not part of a mouse or joystick packet.  By default points to "itsakey."

Made cold-boot RAM clearing faster using a tower of four.
----------------------------
revision 2.21
date: 1990/06/18 16:36:05;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +18 -4
Fixed keyclicks so caps-lock keyclick goes through kcl_hook, not the
built-in keyclick.

----------------------------
revision 2.20
date: 1990/05/09 16:46:58;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +15 -8
Fixed scc tx int code so it works (oops).

Documented a feature of dosound that's always been true: it returns
the current sound-routine pointer, or zero if none.
If the new pointer you pass in is negative, it doesn't change it.
----------------------------
revision 2.19
date: 1990/05/02 16:29:03;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +75 -40
Fixed rsconf so when changing rsmode (flow-control mode): if txoff,
causes a bsr to sender (to wake up the transmission if anything's
buffered), and if rxoff, causes XON or raising RTS.  This didn't work
before.

Changed sender and scc_sender to allow sending the byte at sendnow even
if txoff is set, so you can tell the host to XOFF even if he has told
you to XOFF.
----------------------------
revision 2.18
date: 1990/04/30 18:39:36;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +98 -210
Changed some things in MFP serial port code.  Made kickstart, rsconf
more common to the two MFP's.

When changing rsmode, always clears xoff state and sends XON 
or raises CTS if necessary.

Also fixed rsconf for SCC ports, bits-per-word emulation was wrong.
----------------------------
revision 2.17
date: 1990/03/20 13:33:54;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +15 -3
Bug in Bconmap causes it to fail to detect devno values which are
out of range (higher than maptabsize+6), fixed.
----------------------------
revision 2.16
date: 1990/03/19 16:00:42;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +25 -6
Added comments at Rsconf to the effect that it's always been broken.
No code change for that because it's mostly harmless.

Fixed Bconmap range-check to be (devno >= maxdev) not (devno > maxdev).
Pre-cleared d0 in ttmfp Rsconf when returning baud rate (bug fix).

Added move.l d7,d0 at the end of Rsconf for SCC (bug fix).

Increased Iorec initialization table for SCC to include initial 
baud rate of 1 (9600).
----------------------------
revision 2.15
date: 1990/03/06 15:22:27;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +8 -3
Fixed a fatfinger: if you get a bus error while initting SCC,
the code is supposed to return safely.  Now it does.
----------------------------
revision 2.14
date: 1990/03/02 10:47:58;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +14 -2
Added initialization of ST MFP Timer B to something other than 1.
See startup.s, at the label noblank, for why this is necessary
and not sufficient (!).
----------------------------
revision 2.13
date: 1990/03/01 15:33:46;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +39 -23
Made dowait global; changed delay in ikput to use STMFP Timer C rather
than instructions.  Made bus error during SCC init just return.
Changed some ttwait calls to dowait.
----------------------------
revision 2.12
date: 1990/02/26 17:31:51;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +32 -13
Changed instruction-loop delays to use dowait (see startup) during boot
and another trick in the other place which needs it: ikbdwc. The trick
expects that Timer C is running as we programmed it, but does not rely
on the interrupt being enabled or our handler still handling it.
----------------------------
revision 2.11
date: 1990/02/16 16:43:07;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +829 -35
Added SCC serial-port code to the bconmap section.  All works.

Added initializing registers 9 and 10 to zero in the keyclick-sound
data list, in the hopes that this would fix it: some sounds cause
subsequent keyclicks to come out wrong.  Don't know if this fixes
it or not, because my TT has no speaker!
----------------------------
revision 2.10
date: 1990/02/02 13:37:53;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +769 -55
Added conmap code, and TTMFP serial port code.  The conmap code
should really be dependent on a separate conditional, not TT
as it is now, because it will go in new STe's.  SCC serial-port
driver doesn't exist here yet.

Also changed coldboot to clobber fast RAM, too, again up to
a bus error.
----------------------------
revision 2.9
date: 1989/12/08 15:46:16;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +16 -8
Changed rsconf so it enables & disables tx and rx just by
changing the one bit, not by setting and clearing the whole
tsr/rsr.  This preserves the $5 mode set previously,
so reset & baud-rate changes don't cause spurious chars to be sent.
----------------------------
revision 2.8
date: 1989/10/03 10:03:02;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +29 -5
Changed initialization of MFP's TSR to make the output state
"High" not "Hi-Z" (open collector) when the transmitter is idle.
This finally gets rid of the spurious $ff character transmitted
when you reset an ST.  Also added code to initialize TTMFP's serial
port and set it to 9600 baud.  (No other non-ST serial support yet.)
----------------------------
revision 2.7
date: 1989/09/22 16:39:12;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +509 -489
THIS VERSION REQUIRES TURBO C'S "MAS" ASSEMBLER
No functional changes from previous revision, which is the last to
require Alcyon's AS68 assembler.
----------------------------
revision 2.6
date: 1989/09/12 12:57:08;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +32 -11
Fixed bad initialization of serial port; added dummy read of TSR
at end of txerror as 68901 book suggests; changed use of bclr
when clearing ISR into move with all bits 1 except the one to clear:
this is also required by the 68901 book.
----------------------------
revision 2.5
date: 1989/07/27 18:01:56;  author: apratt;  state: Exp;  lines: +27 -6
Added kcl_hook and bell_hook usage here (usu. they're def_click
